<p>I have a ComVisible COM class written in C#. I want to call it from another C# bit of code using COM and pass the default value for the parameter. I can call plenty of other methods without default arguments.</p>  <p>This is the best I can come up with. The first two lines work for all my other methods.</p>  <pre><code>Type mytype = Type.GetTypeFromProgID("MyType"); dynamic myinstance = Activator.CreateInstance(mytype); object missingValue = System.Reflection.Missing.Value; myinstance.generatecsvdocument("mystring", ref missingValue); </code></pre>  <p>My method looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>public void generatecsvdocument(string mystring, string rowseperator = "\n") </code></pre>  <p>When I run it I get the error:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>The best overloaded method match for 'generatecsvdocument(string,   string)' has some invalid arguments</p> </blockquote>